summary: Do you know just how many times Crowley and Aziraphale call each other “angel” and “dear” in canon? I tried counting during my...
question: Do you know just how many times Crowley and Aziraphale call each other “angel” and “dear” in canon? I tried counting during my last reread (saturday) but I feel like I lost count bc it didn’t seem like very many times at all…
answer:
Hi there, anon!  As it happens, I do know the answer off the top of my head:

Aziraphale calls Crowley my dear once and my dear boy once as well.  Never just dear; it always has my before it and / or boy following.  Each example, I think, is taken as blanket evidence that these are things Aziraphale must call Crowley reasonably often, as comfortably as he uses them.

Crowley calls Aziraphale angel twice.  The same representative casual, comfortable use applies.  The parallelism is lovely; they each call each other by their endearments for each other the same number of times.

summary: I’m rereading Good Omens to pass the time until May 31st, and I completely forgot the joke that there’s a copy in the Vatican....
body: I’m rereading Good Omens to pass the time until May 31st, and I completely forgot the joke that there’s a copy in the Vatican. All I can imagine is the Pope sitting in his office reading it and some cardinal walking in like, “Your Holiness, we have to leave now. You’ve got a meeting at 3.” And he’s just like, “Not now, John, the antichrist and the angel and the demon. You understand. One more paragraph I promise.” And the cardinal just sighs and says, “Holy Father, you’ve said that eight times now. Come on, you can read in the car.” And the Pope just laughs.

summary: Live in Three...Two...Love
title: Live in Three...Two...Love
body:
read it on the AO3 at https://ift.tt/2FnY7YS

by BuLlEtNiPpLeS, CrowleyLovesUSUK

Awkward, chubby teenager Sam Winchester spent his high school years enduring endless bullying, mostly from his secret crush, Gabriel Novak, older brother of Sam’s best friend Cas. Twenty years later, Sam is grown up, successful, and has a rock hard six pack—but he refuses to date, too skittish due to his past. When his older brother Dean musters out of the Army, he convinces Sam to join him and sign up to be on the nation’s hottest reality dating show. Sam reluctantly goes along with his brother’s plan, hoping to simply earn enough ‘easy money’ to pay off his student loans. Once on set, living in a luxurious Montana Ranch, Sam begins to relax and finally enjoy himself…until HE walks out.
Who knew that the ‘bachelor’ they were vying for would be none other than the man that Sam could never seem to get over—Gabriel Novak.
